Confirm that an SUT-style data frame conserves energy.

Source: R/energy_balance.R
verify_SUT_energy_balance_with_units.Rd

If energy is in balance for every row, .sutdata is returned with two additional columns, and execution returns to the caller. If energy balance is not observed for one or more rows, a warning is emitted, and columns named SUT_prod_energy_blance and SUT_ind_energy_blance are added to .sutdata. FALSE indicates energy is not in balance.

verify_SUT_energy_balance_with_units(.sutdata = NULL, U = "U",
  V = "V", Y = "Y", S_units = "S_units", tol = 1e-06,
  SUT_prod_energy_balance = ".SUT_prod_energy_balance",
  SUT_ind_energy_balance = ".SUT_ind_energy_balance")

Arguments

.sutdata

an SUT-style data frame containing columns U, V, Y, and S_units.
U

the name of the column that contains U matrices
V

the name of the column that contains V matrices
Y

the name of the column that contains Y matrices
S_units

the name of the column that contains S_units matrices
tol

the maximum amount by which energy can be out of balance
SUT_prod_energy_balance

the name of the output column that tells whether product balance is OK. Default is ".SUT_prod_energy_balance"
SUT_ind_energy_balance

the name of the output column that tells whether industry balance is OK. Default is ".SUT_ind_energy_balance"

Value

.sutdata with additional columns.

Details

This function should be called for its side-effect of testing whether energy is in balance in .sutdata.

Both product and industry energy balance are verified. Units (as supplied by the S_units matrix) are respected.

Examples

library(magrittr)
library(tidyr)
verify_SUT_energy_balance_with_units(UKEnergy2000mats %>%
                                       spread(key = matrix.name, value = matrix))
